##Shanghai's sleuths are on a tear as they search for a confirmed case

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Huang Xing Labor Watch

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Rodong Sinmun reporter takes you on a fascinating journey through the history of epidemiology.

At the moment, twice a day, Shanghai releases the number of confirmed and suspected cases of new pneumonia. As well as focusing on the ups and downs of the data, there's also the question of the trajectory of every confirmed and suspected patient. Where have they been? Who were you in contact with? Will it cross paths with my life?

On the face of it, the patient's trajectory is a few simple places, but how did these sites and their close contacts come to light? A quick test: Can you remember where you were yesterday and what you did? And a week ago? Two weeks ago? The further I go, the more I forget. The The Silkworm, the simulation, and ultimately the piecing together of human words into complete patient trajectories, is what epidemiologists do.

In order to restore the mysterious flow of work, Labor newspaper reporters came to the Minhang district CDC squatting, with these "detectives" experienced a wonderful "mapping" trip.

TIME: February 18,14:40
Venue: MINHANG DISTRICT CDC General Duty Room

"Hong Hong, you are in charge of this case, he has been to the five hospitals before, with fever symptoms. " On the first floor, in the General Duty Room, the duty officer Jin Baofang handed Chen Hong, the transfer officer, a list of suspected cases faxed from the fifth people's Hospital.

MINHANG DISTRICT CDC mobile team has 42 people, they are responsible for the transfer of all medical institutions in the district. Chen Honghong is one of them.

She quickly reviewed the basic facts about the suspected patient, and sprinted to the emergency supplies room, changed into a white coat, and pulled out a pull-lever suitcase.

This box is the flow of Chen hong-hong transfer package. "10 disposable masks, 2 N95 masks, 2 protective suits, 1 bottle of hand sanitizer... " she quickly counts supplies, grabs another laptop and a sample box and heads for the yard.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the courtyard, a squad car was waiting for her. Half an hour later, she will arrive at the city's fifth people's Hospital to complete an epidemiological history survey of suspected patient Xiao Zhu and bring back a test sample.

Get in the car and sit tight, Chen Hong Hong immediately open the computer, the finger quickly input case information. This is her experience after joining the transfer work. According to the regulations, from the moment she received the notification from the hospital, she must complete the core flow of information report within 2 hours and submit a full report within 24 hours. Excluding the time spent on the way, she was given less than an hour to complete the core entry.

Time Split Second. On the bumpy bus, Chen Honghong filled out forms as he compared them to the outpatient list. His body and computer swayed from side to side as the car swayed.

Time: 18 February 15:46
Venue: Shanghai Fifth People's Hospital

The first time I came to Wu Yuan to do a tune, I lost my way. In a roundabout way, Chen Honghong finally found a quiet office, dial a suspected case of small Zhu's phone. She unrolled an A4 blank sheet of paper that would faithfully record all the time points for the next hour.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At the heart of the Epidemiological History Survey is tracking the movement of the case 14 days before the onset of symptoms. Zhu was sent to a concentration camp by community workers on Feb. 13. Between January 27th and February 5th, he and his wife were away visiting relatives. On a piece of paper, Chen quickly lists a timeline, January 27th, February 14th, followed by a list of people and activities.

"who were you with during your visit, where were you going? " "How did you get to the train station, what bus did you take? " "Have you ever been to a public place? Like a supermarket, a park... " was the most frequently asked question. All questions revolve around "when, where, and WHO. ".

"I, I really do not remember. " When asked about one of the specific activities of the day, the phone at the end of the small Juka Shell. His mind was in a whirl about what had happened two weeks before, and besides, it was his first time there, and he could not remember all the places.

"Don't worry, is he out shopping with his wife? Did he take a walk in the community? " Chen Hong Hong feels the conversation is stuck in a dead end, try to create a workable scenario that mimics the action. "You can look at a cell phone photo, maybe there's a record of it. "

"Turn around in the community, mainly to accompany his parents-in-law. Usually cooking is also their responsibility. " With Chen Honghong guidance, small Zhu seems to remember something. "Have you and your wife ever gone out to buy food? " Chen Hong Hong again put forward a kind of possibility.

"No. "

"What did you do when you returned to Shanghai on February 6? "

"I. . . I still can't remember... " speaking of which, Little Zhu began to get anxious.

Feeling Small Zhu emotional changes, Chen Hong changed the way of direct inquiry, began to pull up the daily. "It's been a long time since I've been home. Do you have any food left? "

"WENT TO GO! " As if all of a sudden opened the door of memory, small Zhu began to say the itinerary details..
"What's The market address? What time did you get there? "

"I check... " under Chen Hong Hong's reminder, Small Zhu through pay treasure bill found the exact time and place of the day. Chen Hong Hung a heart finally put down.

There are many other small ways to guide patients'memories in the course of an epidemiological history survey. For example, through the mobile phone payment certificate, notes, you can find specific time and place. Photographs can also be used to trace movements or trigger memories. If there is still no way to determine, to the patient's family as a breakthrough, patients and family members to recall the scene, step-by-step guidance, but also step-by-step verification.

17:2618 February
Location: Service Vehicle

It was sunny when I left the CDC, and The Sundowners when I left. On the car, Chen Hong Hong is the first thing is to take out the mineral water, Mengchui. An hour of "talking" , without a minute's pause, she was already parched and Hoarse.

After a slight delay, Chen Hong Hong began to fill in the form again, in the previous record form on the circle key.

An accurate and complete flow report must record in detail all the patients'activities at each time point and form a complete chain of evidence. This means that the patient's course of action must stand up to scrutiny, act logically, and be as detailed as possible at every step. Any lack of detail could set back the report.

Chen Hong is used to on the return journey to begin to resume the whole track of activities. Because patient memory often have deviation, retake will find its behavior logic is not smooth, once see the problem, flow dispatchers can contact the patient or family in the first time to review the situation.

TIME: February 1900:38
Venue: MINHANG DISTRICT CDC General Duty Room

Input the last space, the Mouse Click "save" , Xiaozhu's epidemiological history of the investigation report finally completed. Chen hong-chang heaved a sigh. Only then did she realize that she was hungry, so she took out a bowl of instant noodles from a nearby cupboard. Staying up late to eat late supper is her long-standing habit of working overtime.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In fact, it wasn't the first time Chen Hong had worked late into the morning. For mobile operators, 24-hour standby duty is a common occurrence. The time is often concentrated in the afternoon, or even in the early morning. If you get a suspicious case message from the hospital, you need to leave immediately. Since the outbreak, the transfer task is very heavy, team members are conscious of waiting at the CDC, just to reduce the travel time.

The map, which had taken more than nine hours, was quickly reported in the early hours of the day. A few hours later, the day was bright, a small Zhu around the patient epidemic prevention battle in all corners of the city started.
